1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 22=

3
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:48,210
Oh, you're awake?

4
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:49,980
Come over here and have some breakfast.

5
00:01:50,460 --> 00:01:51,930
Grandma sent these biscuits.

6
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:54,490
I made them with lard and
preserved greens. They're great.

7
00:01:56,540 --> 00:01:57,540
What time is it?

8
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,888
(Meeting Minutes, Copy)
Shouldn't you be on the train by now?

9
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:02,570
(Client List)

10
00:02:02,570 --> 00:02:04,540
I woke up too early.
I'm going back to sleep.

11
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:07,380
It's seven o'clock.

12
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,290
I only got up

13
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:10,660
to enjoy a nice breakfast.

14
00:02:10,660 --> 00:02:11,850
Come and have some, too.

15
00:02:13,060 --> 00:02:14,500
That's weird.

16
00:02:15,410 --> 00:02:18,260
You used to race to work
like you were on a rocket.

17
00:02:18,688 --> 00:02:20,890
Why are you suddenly
giving yourself a break today?

18
00:02:20,940 --> 00:02:22,690
You didn't get fired
by Lou Yue, did you?

19
00:02:22,820 --> 00:02:23,730
Touch wood!

20
00:02:23,940 --> 00:02:24,890
Don't jinx me.

21
00:02:25,290 --> 00:02:26,610
I just need to

22
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,570
slow down
and catch my breath occasionally.

23
00:02:29,010 --> 00:02:30,220
I've got to think

24
00:02:30,340 --> 00:02:32,060
about everything that's been happening.

25
00:02:33,220 --> 00:02:36,100
Deep in thought
first thing in the morning?

26
00:02:39,820 --> 00:02:41,130
Are you thinking about him?

27
00:02:42,820 --> 00:02:44,266
I wasn't thinking about Shen Xiezhi.

28
00:02:44,570 --> 00:02:46,010
I didn't say it was him.

29
00:02:48,130 --> 00:02:49,690
Aren't you a doctor? How can you eat

30
00:02:49,690 --> 00:02:50,890
without brushing your teeth?

31
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:55,170
Stop nagging.
It isn't going in your mouth.

32
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,850
Doctors are human too.

33
00:02:57,060 --> 00:02:58,260
Can't the joy of eating

34
00:02:58,260 --> 00:02:59,755
occasionally beat hygiene standards?

35
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,450
Give me a break.

36
00:03:01,450 --> 00:03:02,820
Don't try to change the subject.

37
00:03:04,060 --> 00:03:05,130
Yesterday,

38
00:03:05,170 --> 00:03:05,850
you went

39
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:07,980
to that cafe
right across from the court.

40
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:10,610
Did it keep you up last night?

41
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:15,220
If you've got regrets,
it's not too late.

42
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,980
He hasn't reported for duty yet, right?

43
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:19,760
What nonsense are you talking about?

44
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:22,060
I didn't sleep because

45
00:03:22,100 --> 00:03:24,410
I was thinking
about the Ren Haiping case.

46
00:03:25,010 --> 00:03:26,820
But the court already
granted the divorce.

47
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:28,410
What I suspect and whether or not

48
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:29,220
the divorce is real

49
00:03:29,220 --> 00:03:30,060
don't matter at all.

50
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,260
I've got no evidence.

51
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:33,730
But if this blows up,

52
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,380
it's going to be a disaster.

53
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:39,500
My boss has already given the order,

54
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:41,170
so there's nothing I can do.

55
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:42,940
I just think if something happens,

56
00:03:43,170 --> 00:03:45,100
I need to have all my files ready.

57
00:03:45,422 --> 00:03:47,022
At least be prepared for the worst.

58
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:50,260
You're just guessing at this point.

59
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,340
Seriously.

60
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:55,540
Stop frowning.

61
00:03:55,850 --> 00:03:57,100
You've got such a pretty face.

62
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:58,340
Frowning doesn't suit you.

63
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:01,610
I feel like you're

64
00:04:01,610 --> 00:04:03,066
less happy now than when you were

65
00:04:03,111 --> 00:04:04,688
hustling for cases at the court gates.

66
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,940
It isn't that I'm unhappy.

67
00:04:07,290 --> 00:04:08,500
I'm frowning

68
00:04:09,010 --> 00:04:10,540
because I'm focused. Don't you know?

69
00:04:10,730 --> 00:04:11,980
Details are everything.

70
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,940
Even at a big firm,

71
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:16,580
the highlights always come with shadows.

72
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:18,410
Since I'm already at Ronghe,

73
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:20,460
I've got to make a real name for myself.

74
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:31,340
(Qingcheng District People's Court)

75
00:04:31,370 --> 00:04:32,340
Shi Xiaomei.

76
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:34,250
That's enough.

77
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,460
You want all three kids?

78
00:04:36,490 --> 00:04:37,580
On what grounds?

79
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:38,850
You don't earn a cent.

80
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:40,700
Are you holding them hostage

81
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,460
to squeeze child support
out of my parents?

82
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:43,900
Those three children

83
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:45,250
came from my own body.

84
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:46,370
I'm not letting them go.

85
00:04:48,170 --> 00:04:49,250
I'll grant the divorce,

86
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:50,850
but on one condition.

87
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:53,220
All three kids

88
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,250
stay with me.

89
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:57,140
You're clearly
just trying to wear me down.

90
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:58,900
Is it really that you can't leave them,

91
00:04:58,930 --> 00:05:00,810
or are you just afraid
of losing your lifestyle?

92
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:02,850
You can have more kids
with Hu Xiaoling.

93
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:04,490
What are you talking about?

94
00:05:08,980 --> 00:05:11,140
I've already got three!
Why would I want more?

95
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,220
To tell you the truth,

96
00:05:13,288 --> 00:05:14,220
those two younger ones,

97
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,777
if it weren't for my dad back then...

98
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:17,410
Enough. Let me say something.

99
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,050
Xiaomei.

100
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:21,900
Be honest with me.

101
00:05:21,980 --> 00:05:24,100
In all the years you've been with us,

102
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:26,370
have I ever treated you poorly?

103
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:30,250
Mom.

104
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,460
I know.

105
00:05:32,460 --> 00:05:32,930
Our family

106
00:05:32,930 --> 00:05:34,980
has lived off of you all these years.

107
00:05:35,955 --> 00:05:36,810
But the children...

108
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:38,140
If you two want a divorce,

109
00:05:38,410 --> 00:05:39,490
fine by me.

110
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:42,810
But taking all three kids

111
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:44,050
away from us?

112
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:46,250
You're going to be the death of me.

113
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:52,020
I'm only telling you this
for your own good.

114
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:53,660
Take one with you,

115
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:56,700
and it won't be hard
to start over later.

116
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:58,660
But if you take

117
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,140
the younger two as well,

118
00:06:00,140 --> 00:06:02,490
you'll ruin your entire life.

119
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:05,460
Mom.

120
00:06:05,810 --> 00:06:06,810
I'll tell you right now.

121
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:08,930
I'm never

122
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:10,340
getting married again.

123
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:11,340
Enough of that.

124
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:12,780
Good grief,

125
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,780
why are you being so stubborn?

126
00:06:15,580 --> 00:06:17,220
Let me make this clear.

127
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:19,610
You can take Du, the oldest.

128
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:21,170
But as for the younger ones,

129
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:22,850
don't even think about it.

130
00:06:23,100 --> 00:06:24,810
They're staying with the Duan family.

131
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:28,660
We've been family for so many years.

132
00:06:28,911 --> 00:06:30,170
As mother and daughter-in-law,

133
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,290
I really don't want to make things ugly.

134
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:35,140
But if you insist
on being this stubborn,

135
00:06:35,930 --> 00:06:38,490
don't blame me for being heartless.

136
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:41,220
No matter where this case goes

137
00:06:41,220 --> 00:06:42,850
or who sits on that bench,

138
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:44,170
there's no way

139
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:46,100
you're getting all three kids.

140
00:06:47,370 --> 00:06:48,340
Judge,

141
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:49,580
am I right?

142
00:06:51,290 --> 00:06:53,220
In principle, that's correct.

143
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:55,730
Except for special circumstances.

144
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:58,340
Plaintiff.

145
00:06:58,700 --> 00:06:59,780
Please state your reasons

146
00:06:59,780 --> 00:07:01,488
for wanting custody
of all three children.

147
00:07:01,577 --> 00:07:02,460
Judge,

148
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:05,250
I'm aware

149
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:07,170
that I lack the financial means.

150
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:09,340
The odds of me

151
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:11,460
getting all three are very low.

152
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:13,900
But these three children

153
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:15,730
have grown up by my side.

154
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:17,250
I've never spent a day apart from them.

155
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,370
I can't live without them,
and I can't let them go.

156
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:22,540
Please, Judge,

157
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:26,580
understand how a mother feels.

158
00:07:28,290 --> 00:07:29,050
We understand

159
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:30,610
how you feel as a mother.

160
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:33,170
But you also have to face reality.

161
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,930
If you take all three,

162
00:07:35,730 --> 00:07:37,580
can you really provide for them?

163
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:41,490
Do you hear that?

164
00:07:42,290 --> 00:07:44,140
The judge is right.

165
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:46,580
You say you want all three,

166
00:07:47,930 --> 00:07:49,250
but you have zero income.

167
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:50,340
How will you raise them?

168
00:07:50,490 --> 00:07:53,140
You're obviously
just after more child support

169
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:54,220
so you can live a high life.

170
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:55,170
You want to use them

171
00:07:55,170 --> 00:07:56,580
to maintain your current lifestyle.

172
00:07:56,610 --> 00:07:58,050
To be honest,

173
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,140
my parents' money

174
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:00,730
doesn't exactly grow on trees.

175
00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:04,140
Honestly.

176
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,700
Judge.

177
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:11,980
Judge,

178
00:08:11,980 --> 00:08:13,170
what's with that look?

179
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:14,730
Did I say something wrong?

180
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:15,930
No.

181
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:18,020
Are you trying to insult me
or something?

182
00:08:19,050 --> 00:08:20,050
No, not at all.

183
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:21,730
I'm so sorry.

184
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:23,170
I think I might've eaten something

185
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,755
this morning that didn't agree with me.

186
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:34,700
Lawyer,

187
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,460
I think the judge might be pregnant.

188
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:37,755
We should request someone else.

189
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:38,700
Mr. Duan...

190
00:08:38,700 --> 00:08:39,730
This is a court of law.

191
00:08:40,370 --> 00:08:42,460
Do you want to replace
the panel while you're at it?

192
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:45,420
We also need to hear
what the children have to say.

193
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:47,900
(Ladies' Room)

194
00:09:17,610 --> 00:09:18,490
Mean woman!

195
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:19,420
Hey, there...

196
00:09:19,466 --> 00:09:20,530
Sweetie, try to stay calm.

197
00:09:20,530 --> 00:09:22,130
I don't want to be away from my mom!

198
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:23,533
- I want to be with her!
- Calm down!

199
00:09:23,555 --> 00:09:24,730
And stay with my brother!

200
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:25,700
Bad lady!

201
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,770
Cut it out, little one.

202
00:09:26,770 --> 00:09:28,250
I won't let you separate us!

203
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:29,333
No one is taking you away.

204
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,060
No!

205
00:09:30,060 --> 00:09:31,420
I'm not leaving my mom!

206
00:09:31,420 --> 00:09:32,420
What happened?

207
00:09:32,730 --> 00:09:34,890
You're a bad lady too! Get out!

208
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:35,340
Me?

209
00:09:35,340 --> 00:09:37,460
I'm not leaving my mom!

210
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:39,340
You're all mean!

211
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:41,180
You'll never split us up!

212
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:48,250
"Mean woman..."

213
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:50,820
I guess I am a bad lady.

214
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:52,700
Don't let it get to you.

215
00:09:53,580 --> 00:09:55,530
She's just a child, after all.

216
00:09:56,010 --> 00:09:57,100
Don't take it personally.

217
00:09:57,730 --> 00:09:59,220
It's not that I'm offended.

218
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:01,650
It's just that...

219
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,580
I think she might be right.

220
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:07,460
Since when did you
become so sentimental?

221
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:08,820
This isn't like you.

222
00:10:09,010 --> 00:10:10,730
Maybe it's the pregnancy.

223
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:12,130
I can empathize now.

224
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:14,060
I do have some sympathy

225
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:15,610
for Shi Xiaomei.

226
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:16,940
But at the same time,

227
00:10:16,940 --> 00:10:19,420
I'm frustrated
that she didn't fight for herself.

228
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:22,460
She was a master's student
with a bright future.

229
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:24,300
Her career was just about to take off.

230
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:25,250
Then, she just quit.

231
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:26,420
Look at her now.

232
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:28,250
She doesn't have a penny of her own.

233
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:30,940
She's left her entire fate
in the hands of others.

234
00:10:32,770 --> 00:10:34,130
She can't do anything

235
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:35,700
except wait for

236
00:10:35,700 --> 00:10:36,850
her mother-in-law's mercy.

237
00:10:37,490 --> 00:10:38,980
As for her love for her kids?

238
00:10:39,311 --> 00:10:40,890
Besides some yelling and a few tears,

239
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:43,180
she has no way to prove it.

240
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:44,980
Sometimes I wonder

241
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,130
if it's just like her husband said.

242
00:10:47,370 --> 00:10:49,490
Does she want all three children

243
00:10:49,530 --> 00:10:50,888
just so she can squeeze

244
00:10:50,955 --> 00:10:52,850
more child support out of her in-laws?

245
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:54,250
In our line of work,

246
00:10:54,370 --> 00:10:56,300
we deal with the worst
of human nature every day.

247
00:10:56,850 --> 00:10:58,730
If you expect the worst

248
00:10:58,890 --> 00:11:00,300
but strive for the best outcome,

249
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:01,890
things usually turn out okay.

250
00:11:03,650 --> 00:11:05,610
I considered awarding

251
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,311
both younger children to the mother.

252
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,022
Since they're so young,

253
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,580
lacking maternal love

254
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:12,340
could leave them with lifelong scars.

255
00:11:13,266 --> 00:11:14,466
But I realized I haven't

256
00:11:14,533 --> 00:11:15,580
looked at this

257
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:17,370
from the children's perspective.

258
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:19,340
They've grown up together

259
00:11:19,340 --> 00:11:21,490
as blood siblings.

260
00:11:21,490 --> 00:11:23,420
They aren't just vegetables

261
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:25,580
lined up on a table.

262
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:26,580
We can't simply weigh

263
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,250
and compare them

264
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:29,340
to make it even.

265
00:11:29,850 --> 00:11:32,370
They say family matters are
the hardest to settle,

266
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:34,610
but we have to face the challenge.

267
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:37,340
If the children are young
or have clear preferences,

268
00:11:37,340 --> 00:11:38,580
we just have to consider

269
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:40,250
the best interests of the child.

270
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:41,370
Otherwise,

271
00:11:41,610 --> 00:11:42,370
even though

272
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:44,300
there are more factors
with multiple children,

273
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:46,060
it's fair to give each parent one child

274
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:47,890
when there is a dispute.

275
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:49,850
If there's no dispute,

276
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:51,100
then awarding both to the side

277
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,770
with more financial stability

278
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:54,250
or a stronger desire to parent

279
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:55,130
is perfectly

280
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:56,060
reasonable.

281
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:57,530
But in this case,

282
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:59,060
awarding all the children

283
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:00,460
to one side

284
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:02,180
