for the court to support.

565
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:38,810
I know.

566
00:24:40,570 --> 00:24:42,810
I know it's extremely difficult.

567
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:45,090
But I raised them

568
00:24:45,250 --> 00:24:46,700
all by myself.

569
00:24:47,530 --> 00:24:48,330
No,

570
00:24:48,420 --> 00:24:49,620
to be precise,

571
00:24:49,940 --> 00:24:51,730
Du helped me raise them.

572
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,140
When I was pregnant,

573
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:56,770
my husband never even came home.

574
00:24:57,620 --> 00:24:58,860
These two little ones

575
00:25:00,090 --> 00:25:02,010
don't understand anything yet.

576
00:25:02,660 --> 00:25:04,050
If they realized they're about to be

577
00:25:04,770 --> 00:25:06,380
separated from their sister...

578
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:24,380
I...

579
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:26,770
I'm a useless mother.

580
00:25:27,730 --> 00:25:29,660
I'm so incompetent.

581
00:25:33,660 --> 00:25:34,700
I'm a failure.

582
00:25:38,730 --> 00:25:40,090
They're just children.

583
00:25:41,290 --> 00:25:42,860
They're flesh and blood.

584
00:25:43,010 --> 00:25:44,810
They've grown up together since birth.

585
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:47,380
They've never been apart.

586
00:25:47,810 --> 00:25:48,810
Judge,

587
00:25:49,010 --> 00:25:51,860
surely they have to consider
the children's feelings.

588
00:25:51,980 --> 00:25:53,770
Consider their emotional bond.

589
00:25:59,530 --> 00:26:00,660
I don't know

590
00:26:01,770 --> 00:26:03,570
how to even tell them.

591
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,700
They didn't do anything wrong.

592
00:26:09,810 --> 00:26:12,090
They haven't made a single mistake.

593
00:26:12,290 --> 00:26:13,330
Just because

594
00:26:13,330 --> 00:26:15,810
their parents are getting a divorce,

595
00:26:16,220 --> 00:26:17,250
they'll...

596
00:26:17,810 --> 00:26:19,380
They'll be forced to

597
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:22,490
stay apart forever.

598
00:26:26,010 --> 00:26:27,420
Please, try to stay calm.

599
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:29,380
Here's the thing.

600
00:26:30,250 --> 00:26:32,660
When it comes to custody
of multiple children in a divorce,

601
00:26:33,090 --> 00:26:35,140
the emotional bond between siblings

602
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:37,770
has never been a priority factor.

603
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:39,010
Perhaps

604
00:26:39,010 --> 00:26:40,620
as circumstances change,

605
00:26:40,644 --> 00:26:42,311
there will be more consideration for it.

606
00:26:44,570 --> 00:26:45,490
But,

607
00:26:46,140 --> 00:26:47,140
isn't there

608
00:26:47,770 --> 00:26:49,420
any other option

609
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:50,730
I can take?

610
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:53,620
According to the relevant laws,

611
00:26:53,700 --> 00:26:55,730
a judge will only
exercise their discretion

612
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:58,700
in very exceptional circumstances.

613
00:26:59,090 --> 00:27:00,140
For instance,

614
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,980
if the other parent has

615
00:27:02,140 --> 00:27:04,290
an illness that makes them
unfit to raise a child,

616
00:27:04,810 --> 00:27:06,940
or engages in behavior
harmful to the child.

617
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:09,730
Such as?

618
00:27:09,911 --> 00:27:11,288
For example, domestic violence,

619
00:27:11,810 --> 00:27:13,220
child abuse, and so on.

620
00:27:30,010 --> 00:27:31,700
Mr. Duan, what is the meaning of this?

621
00:27:31,700 --> 00:27:34,060
(Authorized Representative
for the Defendant)

622
00:27:34,090 --> 00:27:35,900
Presiding Judge, she's making this up.

623
00:27:36,140 --> 00:27:37,090
It's a total frame-up.

624
00:27:37,090 --> 00:27:38,420
I've never hit her.

625
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,420
You've never hit me?

626
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:42,490
Even if we fought,

627
00:27:42,490 --> 00:27:43,810
it was a mutual altercation.

628
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:46,770
Do you admit the injuries on the victim

629
00:27:47,090 --> 00:27:48,330
shown in this photo

630
00:27:48,530 --> 00:27:49,490
were caused by you?

631
00:27:51,460 --> 00:27:52,330
Presiding Judge,

632
00:27:52,330 --> 00:27:53,220
even if we did fight,

633
00:27:53,220 --> 00:27:55,050
it was just some pushing and shoving.

634
00:27:55,050 --> 00:27:57,010
It couldn't have
caused injuries like this.

635
00:27:57,250 --> 00:27:58,940
Then, can you explain

636
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:00,570
what caused the marks

637
00:28:00,810 --> 00:28:02,220
in this photograph?

638
00:28:04,220 --> 00:28:05,250
Shi Xiaomei,

639
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:07,755
you're really determined
to make things ugly, aren't you?

640
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:09,900
Maintain courtroom decorum.

641
00:28:10,460 --> 00:28:12,220
Unless this court has
granted you the floor,

642
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:13,490
please do not interrupt.

643
00:28:13,810 --> 00:28:14,290
Your Honor,

644
00:28:14,290 --> 00:28:15,977
(Courtroom 1, Camera 4)
I must explain.

645
00:28:16,044 --> 00:28:17,420
My son is being framed.

646
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,140
When she was pregnant
with the twins,

647
00:28:20,180 --> 00:28:22,220
my son never even came home.

648
00:28:22,220 --> 00:28:23,090
He...

649
00:28:23,380 --> 00:28:25,050
How could he have abused her?

650
00:28:27,140 --> 00:28:29,090
We originally wanted them
to have more kids

651
00:28:29,250 --> 00:28:31,090
to save the marriage,

652
00:28:31,140 --> 00:28:32,620
but then

653
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:34,380
the arguments just got worse.

654
00:28:34,577 --> 00:28:36,555
On the babies' 100th-day celebration,

655
00:28:37,770 --> 00:28:39,530
those two had a massive blowout.

656
00:28:39,530 --> 00:28:40,660
My son...

657
00:28:40,730 --> 00:28:41,770
How could he have possibly

658
00:28:41,770 --> 00:28:44,220
come back just to hit her again?

659
00:28:45,380 --> 00:28:46,290
Shi Xiaomei,

660
00:28:46,770 --> 00:28:49,290
even if you have issues with my son,

661
00:28:49,490 --> 00:28:51,660
you can't just frame him!

662
00:28:53,050 --> 00:28:55,090
You could have retribution for this!

663
00:28:55,090 --> 00:28:56,090
Ms. Feng,

664
00:28:56,155 --> 00:28:58,044
(Presiding Judge)
please control your emotions.

665
00:28:59,380 --> 00:29:00,700
You know better than anyone

666
00:29:00,700 --> 00:29:02,250
how you got those marks.

667
00:29:03,050 --> 00:29:04,050
Honestly.

668
00:29:06,090 --> 00:29:06,940
Plaintiff,

669
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:09,330
can you prove that the defendant

670
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:11,530
indeed caused the injuries in the photo?

671
00:29:16,010 --> 00:29:17,250
I'm sorry, Judge.

672
00:29:19,420 --> 00:29:20,290
I...

673
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:25,140
I just wanted to
keep my children with me so badly.

674
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:29,250
I really have been abused before.

675
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:31,770
But...

676
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:34,490
I wasn't able to keep any evidence.

677
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:40,620
Then, what is this in the photograph?

678
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:44,490
It's purpura.

679
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:47,090
Plaintiff, please be seated.

680
00:29:49,770 --> 00:29:50,810
It's purpura.

681
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:53,050
I got it after I had the twins.

682
00:29:54,010 --> 00:29:55,180
One touch leaves a huge mark.

683
00:29:55,911 --> 00:29:57,900
Even without a touch,
they appear everywhere.

684
00:29:58,570 --> 00:30:00,380
Whether it's vasculitis

685
00:30:01,180 --> 00:30:02,140
or a skin allergy,

686
00:30:02,140 --> 00:30:04,490
even the doctors
still can't say for sure.

687
00:30:05,460 --> 00:30:06,530
I'm sorry, Judge.

688
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:08,900
I...

689
00:30:08,900 --> 00:30:10,770
I didn't really want to commit perjury.

690
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:12,530
I just...

691
00:30:14,530 --> 00:30:17,380
I just really couldn't
find any other evidence.

692
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:18,180
I...

693
00:30:23,980 --> 00:30:25,010
Duan Ziping is not fit

694
00:30:25,180 --> 00:30:27,140
to be a father!

695
00:30:27,730 --> 00:30:29,530
How could Shi Xiaomei have developed

696
00:30:29,530 --> 00:30:32,180
such obvious purpura after giving birth,

697
00:30:32,330 --> 00:30:33,620
and yet her husband

698
00:30:34,140 --> 00:30:35,050
and mother-in-law

699
00:30:35,090 --> 00:30:36,570
were both completely unaware of it?

700
00:30:36,980 --> 00:30:38,700
Shi Xiaomei had

701
00:30:38,900 --> 00:30:39,730
such a bright future.

702
00:30:39,730 --> 00:30:41,810
Why did she fall
for a guy like Duan Ziping?

703
00:30:42,460 --> 00:30:44,220
Who can say when it comes to love?

704
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:46,490
Let's focus on the children's custody.

705
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:48,010
What do you two think?

706
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:50,860
I'm definitely in favor of awarding

707
00:30:50,860 --> 00:30:52,490
all three children to Shi Xiaomei.

708
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:54,050
Duan Ziping

709
00:30:54,570 --> 00:30:55,940
is just so unreliable.

710
00:30:56,490 --> 00:30:58,270
If the kids aren't split up

711
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,810
and all stay with him,

712
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:01,940
they barely have
a father's love as it is,

713
00:31:02,066 --> 00:31:04,140
and now they'd lose
their mother's love too.

714
00:31:04,810 --> 00:31:05,900
The grandmother said

715
00:31:06,050 --> 00:31:07,010
she'd hire a nanny

716
00:31:07,010 --> 00:31:08,810
to take care of the kids.

717
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:11,010
But is a nanny the same as a mother?

718
00:31:11,010 --> 00:31:12,770
They don't even share a blood bond.

719
00:31:12,900 --> 00:31:15,220
Since Duan Ziping might have cheated,

720
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:16,940
could we lean more towards Shi Xiaomei

721
00:31:17,090 --> 00:31:19,460
in the property division?

722
00:31:19,620 --> 00:31:21,420
I've actually considered that.

723
00:31:22,180 --> 00:31:22,940
First of all,

724
00:31:22,940 --> 00:31:23,980
the couple

725
00:31:23,980 --> 00:31:25,620
has no joint assets.

726
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:27,644
They've been living off the grandmother.

727
00:31:27,980 --> 00:31:28,810
Secondly,

728
00:31:28,810 --> 00:31:30,380
there is no solid evidence

729
00:31:30,380 --> 00:31:32,220
to prove that Duan Ziping cheated.

730
00:31:32,460 --> 00:31:33,900
At most, he failed to fulfill

731
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:35,810
his duty of marital fidelity.

732
00:31:36,490 --> 00:31:39,090
But that isn't enough
to name him the at-fault party.

733
00:31:39,420 --> 00:31:41,900
We can't just let financial factors

734
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:44,570
be the reason all three kids
are separated from their mother.

735
00:31:45,860 --> 00:31:47,420
That's too cruel.

736
00:31:48,730 --> 00:31:49,570
True.

737
00:31:49,810 --> 00:31:52,420
Duan Ziping has never fulfilled

738
00:31:52,770 --> 00:31:53,810
his parental obligations.

739
00:31:54,290 --> 00:31:55,940
That's also one of our considerations.

740
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:58,050
I think Shi Xiaomei's

741
00:31:58,050 --> 00:31:59,140
greatest advantage

742
00:31:59,140 --> 00:32:00,940
is her emotional bond with the children.

743
00:32:01,290 --> 00:32:03,530
Besides, the child has
explicitly expressed

744
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:05,490
the desire to live with her mother.

745
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:06,660
Du is twelve, so we can take

746
00:32:06,810 --> 00:32:07,940
her opinion into account.

747
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:11,050
But the twins are only six years old.

748
00:32:11,290 --> 00:32:12,180
Honestly,

749
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:14,250
Shi Xiaomei
came to her senses far too late.

750
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,770
Had it been a few years earlier,

751
00:32:15,810 --> 00:32:17,250
we could have unconditionally

752
00:32:17,250 --> 00:32:18,660
awarded custody to her.

753
00:32:20,620 --> 00:32:22,250
I actually think Shi Xiaomei

754
00:32:22,420 --> 00:32:23,620
gave up on her career

755
00:32:23,620 --> 00:32:25,090
far too early

756
00:32:25,570 --> 00:32:26,620
to be a housewife.

757
00:32:27,810 --> 00:32:29,330
Perhaps this whole ordeal

758
00:32:29,460 --> 00:32:30,900
will finally wake her up.

759
00:32:31,090 --> 00:32:33,220
She'll realize that she can
only rely on herself.

760
00:32:33,530 --> 00:32:35,010
Only with financial independence

761
00:32:35,140 --> 00:32:36,755
can you have an independent character.

762
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:39,420
But she's been
out of the loop for so long.

763
00:32:40,050 --> 00:32:41,330
Will it be easy to find work?

764
00:32:41,730 --> 00:32:43,460
She's a graduate student, after all.

765
00:32:43,530 --> 00:32:45,050
Even after all these years,

766
00:32:45,050 --> 00:32:47,050
her ability to learn
should still be there.

767
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:49,660
Even so, we can't

768
00:32:49,660 --> 00:32:51,620
award all the kids to her
just because of that.

769
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:54,220
Tell you what.

770
00:32:54,220 --> 00:32:55,420
Let's wait for the next hearing

771
00:32:55,420 --> 00:32:56,420
to see if both parties

772
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:57,980
have any new evidence to submit.

773
00:32:57,980 --> 00:32:59,290
We'll decide then.

774
00:32:59,460 --> 00:33:00,250
Sure.

775
00:33:04,220 --> 00:33:05,460
Duan Ziping...

776
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:21,700
(Another day of learning
the law with Ms. Qin.)

777
00:33:26,260 --> 00:33:27,860
(I envy the rich. They can get help
as long as they pay enough.)

778
00:33:30,780 --> 00:33:33,140
(Curse that capitalist lackey.
She will face the people's wrath.)

779
00:33:35,570 --> 00:33:37,290
(Maybe she didn't know at first.)

780
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:39,220
(Mr. Ren is an old fox, after all.)

781
00:33:39,730 --> 00:33:40,660
(She didn't know?)

782
00:33:40,730 --> 00:33:42,444
(Is she even
a professional lawyer then?)

783
00:33:42,570 --> 00:33:44,380
(She lacks basic
professional intuition.)

784
00:33:44,530 --> 00:33:46,180
(That's a bit harsh.)

785
00:33:46,180 --> 00:33:47,220
(Have some decency.)

786
00:33:47,940 --> 00:33:49,730
(Careful, things might turn around.)

787
00:33:49,810 --> 00:33:52,050
(She might just be a scapegoat.)

788
00:33:52,050 --> 00:33:53,533
(Who can guarantee they're always)

789
00:33:53,577 --> 00:33:54,550
(on the side of justice?)

790
00:33:54,570 --> 00:33:55,770
(Whose side are you on?)

791
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:57,220
(Brainless fan. Get lost.)

792
00:33:57,290 --> 00:33:58,770
(Wait until she bleeds you dry.)

793
00:33:58,770 --> 00:33:59,700
(Then you'll be happy.)

794
00:34:00,010 --> 00:34:00,660
(Exactly.)

795
00:34:00,660 --> 00:34:01,980
(She's cozying up to billionaires.)

796
00:34:01,980 --> 00:34:03,800
(Yet she's pretending
to be a regular worker.)

797
00:34:03,888 --> 00:34:04,810
(How shameless.)

798
00:34:05,330 --> 00:34:06,980
(You're just a greedy little lackey.)

799
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:08,380
(Unfollow and block.)

800
00:34:08,650 --> 00:34:10,940
(I used to think she was a lawyer
with a conscience.)

801
00:34:11,530 --> 00:34:13,130
(Qin Rui isn't a good guy.)

802
00:34:13,130 --> 00:34:14,380
(They are birds of a feather.)

803
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:19,780
Now that it's blown up,
we have to face it.

804
00:34:20,010 --> 00:34:20,940
Deflecting or avoiding

805
00:34:21,010 --> 00:34:22,260
won't solve anything.

806
00:34:22,300 --> 00:34:23,420
(Senior Partner)
Correct.

807
00:34:23,420 --> 00:34:24,940
(Senior Partner, Lou Yue)
Stick to the facts.

808
00:34:25,380 --> 00:34:27,170
After the judgment was rendered,

809
00:34:27,490 --> 00:34:29,050
it wasn't until official news came out

810
00:34:29,130 --> 00:34:30,610
that we knew the divorce was a sham.

811
00:34:31,530 --> 00:34:33,610
The entire representation

812
00:34:33,740 --> 00:34:35,010
was entirely legal and compliant.

813
00:34:35,050 --> 00:34:36,740
We fulfilled our duties as lawyers.

814
00:34:37,210 --> 00:34:38,090
Come in.

815
00:34:39,570 --> 00:34:40,740
Alright, that's it.

816
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:44,900
Ms. Lou.

817
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:46,650
You got the word.

818
00:34:49,210 --> 00:34:50,050
Come in.

819
00:34:56,260 --> 00:34:57,130
Take a seat.

820
00:35:02,090 --> 00:35:03,780
The firm will issue a statement soon

821
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:06,170
to explain
the representation objectively

822
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,300
with a rational voice.

823
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:09,940
I'm afraid a statement now
might backfire.

824
00:35:10,740 --> 00:35:11,900
People are still furious.

825
00:35:12,010 --> 00:35:14,130
It could easily bring heat to the firm.

826
00:35:14,380 --> 00:35:15,740
The damage is already done.

827
00:35:16,130 --> 00:35:17,900
Ronghe Law Firm must take a stand.

828
00:35:18,844 --> 00:35:20,533
We reaped the rewards of the case,

829
00:35:21,050 --> 00:35:22,940
so we have to endure the backlash, too.

830
00:35:23,210 --> 00:35:24,300
I just heard

831
00:35:24,610 --> 00:35:26,130
that Mr. Ren's wife, Ms. Bai,

832
00:35:26,260 --> 00:35:28,490
has also been added as a defendant.

833
00:35:28,690 --> 00:35:29,940
She'll join Mr. Ren in taking

834
00:35:29,980 --> 00:35:31,155
responsibility for the debts.

835
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,300
This process

836
00:35:32,490 --> 00:35:33,650
will take some time.

837
00:35:34,740 --> 00:35:36,460
But I believe the whole situation

838
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:38,170
will move in a positive direction.

839
00:35:39,010 --> 00:35:40,130
For the time being,

840
00:35:40,530 --> 00:35:42,090
it's better if you don't show your face.

841
00:35:45,900 --> 00:35:47,130
I don't quite understand.

842
00:35:55,380 --> 00:35:56,530
I know this is unfair to you.

843
00:35:57,170 --> 00:35:58,260
But believe me,

844
00:35:58,420 --> 00:36:00,130
I'm not trying to make you a scapegoat.

845
00:36:01,130 --> 00:36:02,210
Given how Mr. Ren's case

846
00:36:02,210 --> 00:36:03,530
has unfolded to this point

847
00:36:03,740 --> 00:36:05,444
and the fact that you're caught in this,

848
00:36:05,820 --> 00:36:06,900
I am responsible.

849
00:36:07,650 --> 00:36:08,740
I apologize to you.

850
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:10,940
I'm sorry, Qin Rui.

851
00:36:11,740 --> 00:36:13,420
But right now, we need to use time

852
00:36:13,488 --> 00:36:15,130
to let everyone regain their reason.

853
00:36:15,210 --> 00:36:16,380
Let things cool down.

854
00:36:20,090 --> 00:36:22,490
Everyone previously
involved in this case,

855
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:24,530
you, me, and Ronghe Law Firm,

856
00:36:24,780 --> 00:36:26,860
should keep our public
appearances to a minimum.

857
00:36:27,010 --> 00:36:28,130
Maintain a low profile.

858
00:36:29,170 --> 00:36:30,170
So,

859
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:32,300
I can't work on anything?

860
00:36:32,690 --> 00:36:33,690
Not exactly.

861
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:35,610
Continue with the Hehua case.

862
00:36:35,666 --> 00:36:37,130
It doesn't require court appearances,

863
00:36:37,210 --> 00:36:38,210
so it won't be a problem.

864
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:39,900
For the time being,

865
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:43,050
you'll mainly focus on non-litigation.

866
00:36:43,090 --> 00:36:44,570
Once Mr. Ren's case blows over,

867
00:36:45,130 --> 00:36:46,210
I'll bring you back.

868
00:36:48,260 --> 00:36:49,490
I'll owe you a favor.

869
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:54,260
Sure.

870
00:36:55,260 --> 00:36:56,210
I see the big picture.

871
00:36:57,460 --> 00:36:58,610
I'll follow the arrangement.

872
00:37:08,980 --> 00:37:09,510
Hello?

873
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:10,910
Hello?

874
00:37:11,530 --> 00:37:12,610
Where are you?

875
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:14,010
I'm at the firm.

876
00:37:14,340 --> 00:37:16,130
I saw that video you posted.

877
00:37:17,010 --> 00:37:19,650
The people in the comments
are too nasty.

878
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:23,650
I saw it.

879
00:37:23,780 --> 00:37:25,260
Don't take it to heart.

880
00:37:27,130 --> 00:37:29,210
Bad people still need to eat

881
00:37:29,340 --> 00:37:30,380
and file lawsuits.

882
00:37:30,610 --> 00:37:32,490
You're just doing your job.

883
00:37:32,900 --> 00:37:34,740
If anyone is to blame,
it's Ren Haiping.

884
00:37:34,940 --> 00:37:36,940
Why take it out on you?

885
00:37:37,170 --> 00:37:38,420
It makes me so mad.

886
00:37:38,940 --> 00:37:39,820
It's okay.

887
00:37:40,530 --> 00:37:41,690
They probably think

888
00:37:41,690 --> 00:37:43,170
I'm one of them.

889
00:37:46,530 --> 00:37:47,610
If you take their money,

890
00:37:47,610 --> 00:37:49,010
you have to take the hits.

891
00:37:49,650 --> 00:37:51,050
The anger in the comments

892
00:37:51,530 --> 00:37:52,860
is only temporary.

893
00:37:53,570 --> 00:37:55,650
Once everyone cools down and thinks,

894
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:57,380
the tone might change.

895
00:37:58,090 --> 00:37:59,420
We're all just workers.

896
00:37:59,650 --> 00:38:01,155
Why make life hard for each other?

897
00:38:04,050 --> 00:38:05,130
I know.

898
00:38:06,860 --> 00:38:09,130
Don't let this little thing
discourage you.

899
00:38:09,610 --> 00:38:11,090
(Rui)
You're a lawyer.

900
00:38:11,340 --> 00:38:12,490
Competence is what matters.

901
00:38:12,820 --> 00:38:14,570
Stay capable,
and you'll keep your place.

902
00:38:14,740 --> 00:38:16,380
Nothing else is important.

903
00:38:17,210 --> 00:38:18,380
Don't worry.

904
00:38:19,170 --> 00:38:21,170
When have I ever admitted defeat?

905
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:23,380
Besides,

906
00:38:23,860 --> 00:38:24,900
I've already got one foot

907
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:26,300
in a top-tier law firm.

908
00:38:27,300 --> 00:38:29,610
Is it likely I'd just pack up and leave?

909
00:38:31,170 --> 00:38:32,460
That'd be more embarrassing.

910
00:38:33,860 --> 00:38:35,010
Exactly.

911
00:38:35,050 --> 00:38:37,210
That's the Rui I know.

912
00:38:37,460 --> 00:38:38,940
We can't let a small hurdle

913
00:38:38,940 --> 00:38:40,210
break us.

914
00:38:41,780 --> 00:38:43,340
The nasty comments aren't a big deal.

915
00:38:43,650 --> 00:38:44,610
I'm just glad

916
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:46,090
I didn't end up in jail.

917
00:38:46,940 --> 00:38:48,300
Touch wood!

918
00:38:48,340 --> 00:38:50,300
What are you talking about? Jail time?

919
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:51,460
It's not that serious.

920
00:38:51,780 --> 00:38:53,010
Even if you did go to jail,

921
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:54,340
I'd still bring you meals.

922
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:57,940
I know you're good to me, okay?

923
00:38:58,340 --> 00:38:59,420
You're just realizing that?

924
00:39:00,050 --> 00:39:01,090
Alright.

925
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:03,130
Nothing beats a good meal.

926
00:39:03,866 --> 00:39:04,900
I'll meet up with you,

927
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:06,420
and we'll go out for dinner.

928
00:39:06,420 --> 00:39:07,380
It'll cheer you up.

929
00:39:08,530 --> 00:39:09,260
No need.

930
00:39:09,260 --> 00:39:11,940
I'll just grab a bite on my own.

931
00:39:12,340 --> 00:39:13,650
It's free!

932
00:39:14,050 --> 00:39:16,130
Our alumni association
has an event today.

933
00:39:16,420 --> 00:39:18,860
Fei from the forensic center
can't make it,

934
00:39:19,260 --> 00:39:20,980
so he gave me his meal voucher.

935
00:39:21,210 --> 00:39:23,460
Alright.
I can't let a freebie go to waste.

936
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:24,820
Well,

937
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:26,780
I'm heading back to pick you up now.

938
00:39:26,980 --> 00:39:28,460
Change my clothes and we'll go.

939
00:39:30,130 --> 00:39:31,860
I'd never say no to a beauty.

940
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:34,340
Hurry up, I'm waiting. Bye.

941
00:39:41,460 --> 00:39:43,860
(Your fearless, persistent,)

942
00:39:43,860 --> 00:39:45,010
(and relentless)

943
00:39:45,010 --> 00:39:47,420
(professional persona has
completely crumbled.)

944
00:39:47,530 --> 00:39:48,740
(Buck up.)

945
00:39:49,260 --> 00:39:51,177
(It's too early
for a few sarcastic remarks)

946
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:52,866
(to break you down like this.)

947
00:39:58,020 --> 00:40:00,580
(Mom)

948
00:40:19,620 --> 00:40:22,700
(Mom)

949
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:30,380
What are you doing here?

950
00:40:31,090 --> 00:40:33,650
It's a long night.
I thought you'd be lonely,

951
00:40:33,650 --> 00:40:35,133
so I came over to keep you company.

952
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:49,420
What kind of training is this?

953
00:40:50,380 --> 00:40:52,050
Watching TV with the sound off.

954
00:40:53,644 --> 00:40:54,740
Did you take on a case

955
00:40:54,740 --> 00:40:56,300
that requires lip-reading?

956
00:41:23,780 --> 00:41:27,820
(Tea Party)

957
00:41:27,820 --> 00:41:28,980
It's pretty lively.

958
00:41:29,090 --> 00:41:30,610
Would you like something to drink?

959
00:41:33,380 --> 00:41:34,530
What's the deal?

960
00:41:34,940 --> 00:41:36,530
Why is everyone in pairs?

961
00:41:43,130 --> 00:41:45,130
Welcome to today's event.

962
00:41:45,130 --> 00:41:47,010
There are no restrictions today.

963
00:41:47,010 --> 00:41:47,940
Feel free to pair up.

964
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:49,530
Please sign your names.

965
00:41:49,690 --> 00:41:51,170
Isn't this an alumni event?

966
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:52,980
Why does it look like...

967
00:41:53,340 --> 00:41:55,530
Today is the alumni singles' special.

968
00:41:55,940 --> 00:41:57,940
Make sure to
seize the opportunity today.

969
00:42:04,650 --> 00:42:05,690
We'll sign in ourselves.

970
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:06,866
You can get back to work.

971
00:42:06,888 --> 00:42:08,460
Alright. Have a great time!

972
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,340
Liu Lian!

973
00:42:12,460 --> 00:42:13,650
What is it?

974
00:42:14,010 --> 00:42:15,090
Come here.

975
00:42:15,490 --> 00:42:17,650
Since we're here,
we can't come for nothing.

976
00:42:17,980 --> 00:42:19,010
Seriously.

977
00:42:19,260 --> 00:42:21,210
I'm not in the mood for this.

978
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:23,780
Come back.

979
00:42:24,740 --> 00:42:25,570
Let me ask you.

980
00:42:26,130 --> 00:42:27,210
Are you single?

981
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,650
Am I single?

982
00:42:29,170 --> 00:42:31,210
We're two single adult women

983
00:42:31,210 --> 00:42:33,050
attending a matchmaking party.

984
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:35,530
Isn't that perfectly normal?

985
00:42:36,130 --> 00:42:37,090
Let's go.

986
00:42:38,090 --> 00:42:39,050
What are you doing?

987
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:40,130
Take a look.

988
00:42:41,050 --> 00:42:41,900
Listen.

989
00:42:41,980 --> 00:42:44,780
The room is full of legal professionals.

990
00:42:44,940 --> 00:42:46,650
You can at least meet new people.

991
00:42:46,650 --> 00:42:48,130
Expand your network.

992
00:42:48,130 --> 00:42:49,420
Don't be silly.

993
00:42:51,940 --> 00:42:53,260
I'm going in first.

994
00:42:54,340 --> 00:42:56,050
We shouldn't stick together.

995
00:42:57,090 --> 00:42:59,090
With a bestie around,
who'd dare to flirt?

996
00:43:00,130 --> 00:43:01,090
Don't leave without me.

997
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

998
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

999
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1000
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1001
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1002
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1003
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1004
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1005
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1006
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1007
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1008
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1009
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1010
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1011
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1012
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1013
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1014
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1015
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1016
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1017
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1018
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1019
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1020
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1021
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1022
